results.question: What two actions must be done in the event of spreader failure or stoppage while using the spreader in the field?

- Set the plate using the (online) spreading chart.

results.question: What should I do if the flow of the fertiliser is blocked, at what page should I look?
results.expected_answer: Clean the machine well after each use. Replace the agitator if it is worn out. The page is 118
results.model_answer:
Clean the machine well after each use. Replace the agitator if it is worn out (Page 6).

If you have not found any damage, the failure is probably due to stoppage from an encrusted layer of fertiliser. Try to reduce the size of the lump or encrusted layer with an object such as a stick, screwdriver or vane. Inspect the hopper contents for other lumps and reduce them.
